<TITLE> Bangladesh lose 9-1 to UAE </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com)  After making a flying start against Palestine, Bangladesh Saturday went down 9-1 against hosts United Arab Emirates (UAE) in the AFC Under-16 (Group D) Championship Qualifying round. Bangladesh, who beat Palestine 9-1 in their opener, surprisingly conceded three goals in three minutes of the dying moments at the Military Physical Centre Stadium. Bangladesh went 2-0 down in the first half and conceded another seven goals in the second half as Salman and Ahmed each scored a hat -trick. Ahmed struck hat- trick in the 87th, 88th and 89th minute while Salman scored in the 46th, 52nd and 59th minute. Apart from two hat-tricks, Abdullah netted two goals and Selim scored one goal for the hosts. Shohel struck the lone goal for Bangladesh in the 61st minute. Bangladesh will face Turkmenistan on October 22, Uzbekistan on October 25 and Tajikistan on October 28. The two top teams in the group will qualify for the 16-nation final round. 
